text.tspan: keyswitch is 8.5mm below fixing place - so 6.5mm below plate,
- sides are to be glued to the switch plate, the bottom is removable with bolts.
- no holes on switch plate, switches are enough
- just wooden pegs/walls from pcb to bottom
- only 2 bolts underneath, glued to the pcb (with a washer) so they don't turn
- have enough strength between bottom and pcb
- make hole for usb-c on left side
- add charger to see where it goes
- a reed switch on the pcb will be normally closed, but will open when the case
is on top because it has a magnet in it; (reed switch should be on the far
side from where the case will be used as a hand rest, so not to affect it)
- make sure the usb-c cable can be plugged in when the case is on top
- cover short sides with half hole for usb cable need to be not mirror to each other
- cover is exactly correct size, but sides are too far apart because of natural angle,
so just put cover spacers in the corners, and double them when on sides in middle
- no place for the switch when the cover goes on top
- idea: put a wooden slider on top of the switch, and the cover can have a place
for the wooden slider so it fits when turned off
- test physically if a usb cable with the bulky part can go in when cover on

- only 2 bolts underneath, glued to the pcb (with a washer) so they don't turn

- add charger to see where it goes
- match up usb-c to be flush with the outside of the wooden side
